==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maronite
<hw>Mar"o*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Maronites</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<def>One of a body of nominal Christians, who speak the Arabic language,
and reside on Mount Lebanon and in different parts of Syria. They take
their name from one <persfn><etsep>Maron</etsep></persfn> of the 6th
century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maroon</ent>⟦br⟧
